KitpagesFileBundle (work in progress)
=====================================

This is an ajax upload system for symfony.
It is still in alpha state don't use it in production.

author : Philippe Le Van (@plv)


Installation
============
hum... as usual...

put the code in vendors/Kitpages/FileBundle

add vendors/ in the app/autoload.php

add the new Bundle in app/appKernel.php

You need to create a table in the database :
CREATE TABLE upload_file
    (
        id INT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
        is_private TINYINT(1) NOT NULL,
        file_name VARCHAR(250) NOT NULL,
        is_published TINYINT(1) NOT NULL,
        item_class_name VARCHAR(250),
        item_id INT,
        published_at DATETIME,
        unpublished_at DATETIME,
        createdAt DATETIME NOT NULL,
        updatedAt DATETIME NOT NULL,
        hasUploadFailed TINYINT(1),
        data longtext NOT NULL COMMENT '(DC2Type:array)',
        PRIMARY KEY (id)
    )
    ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

(or you can use php app/console doctrine:schema:update)


Installation AvalancheImagineBundle
============
Step 1
bin/vendors.php

add the following entries to the deps in the root of your project file:

[Imagine]
    git=http://github.com/avalanche123/Imagine.git
    target=imagine

Step2: Configure the autoloader

Add the following entries to your autoloader:

<?php
// app/autoload.php

$loader->registerNamespaces(array(
    // ...

    'Imagine'          => __DIR__.'/../vendor/imagine/lib',
));




